Our perimeter security fence, digital surveillance cameras, and gated entry with access code ensure that only authorized individuals have access to the facility. These features not only offer you peace of mind but also provide round-the-clock monitoring to protect your items.  With Wooster Self Storage, you'll enjoy the convenience you deserve. Our location makes it easy to drop off and pick up your belongings whenever you need them. With drive-up access to your unit, it's easy to load and unload your items without any hassle. Additionally, our facility is accessible 7 days a week, so you never have to worry about not being able to access your items.  Our facility offers month-to-month leases, so you can store your belongings for as long as you need them, without breaking the bank. We offer competitive pricing to ensure that you're getting the best value for your money. Our prices are all-inclusive, so there are no surprise fees or hidden charges. You'll always know exactly what to expect for the amount you're paying.  Our friendly and knowledgeable staff is always available to assist you and answer any questions you may have about our facility. Whether you need help selecting a unit size or want more information about our security measures, we're here to help. We pride ourselves on providing exceptional customer service and making sure that our clients are satisfied throughout their storage experience with us.  Wooster Self Storage is also a green storage facility. Our facility is solar-powered and we recycle wherever possible. We aim to reduce the carbon footprint of our customers while providing them with the best possible storage experience.  Overall, Wooster Self Storage is the ideal choice for anyone in need of secure and convenient storage in Wooster, Ohio. With a variety of unit sizes, state-of-the-art security features, competitive pricing, and exceptional customer service, you can rest assured that your belongings are in good hands. Description: ClosetDash is the social way for women to swap and shop for pre-loved fashion.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Shop and Swap and Fashions You Love! We’ve all been there: The mad dash of a sample sale, grabbing anything just because it’s 70% off only to be left with a handful of clothes that just don’t work. Now they sit in your closet mocking you for your impulse purchase while taking up valuable real estate. You don’t want to donate them (they’ve still got tags on!) but the thought of posting it to an auction site exhausts you. And forget the consignment shops with their high fees, unpredictable sales and strict acceptance policies.  So why not swap those items for something you’ll actually use? Enter ClosetDash to save the day! Recently featured in New York Magazine, ClosetDash is the first and ONLY shop dedicated to shopping and swapping brand-name Women’s Apparel, Shoes and Bags. It takes the consignment shop model to the next level by giving full credit to shoppers to swap their items for items at ClosetDash! The practice of swapping has numerous benefits for the economy, the environment, and for individuals. During these frugal times, swapping helps budget conscious individuals upcycle their goods and get new items, while creating more efficient uses for their possessions. Swapping also has long-reaching effect on the manufacturing industry by decreasing the demand for water, energy and raw materials as the need for new items diminishes. Best of all it gives individuals a sense of accomplishment and excitement when they know their items are in better hands, and a little reward for themselves as well since they get to take home a new treasure!

Description: 9-1-1 Labs creates consumer, commercial, and white-label products and technologies for the public safety marketplace.
Full Description: 9-1-1 Labs creates consumer, commercial, and white-label products and technologies for the public safety marketplace. Drawing on the experience of its founder’s thirty years of experience in public safety both on the “front line” as a paramedic, firefighter, and 9-1-1 center director, as well as in senior technical architecture roles for some of the major commercial providers in the industry, the company is actively developing new technology for consumers, public safety agencies, and for the Next Generation 9-1-1 industry. The company’s primary consumer product is a patent-pending application for connecting schools and caregivers to parents in urgent and emergent situations.  FamAlert is a SaaS application that allows a family to provision a unique telephone number to be given out as the primary emergency contact for a student.  When called, the system simultaneously calls one or more tiers of designated contacts, connecting all those that answer into a conference call in order to manage the emergency. Tactical Event is the company’s initial public safety agency offering.  The SaaS/Mobile applications streamline event planning and real-time dispatch and management for major planned and unplanned events, a special and underserved segment of the public safety marketplace. 9-1-1 Labs also develops both front-end and back-end systems, user interfaces, and software for the coming Next Generation 9-1-1 network, on behalf of its industry partners and clients.

Headquarters Regions: Greater Miami Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Founded in 1988, American Factor is a family-run business that specializes in purchasing invoices from growth companies in service and product industries. American Factor has no size restrictions for these companies. In fact, most of our clientele have less than $1 million in annual sales. Whereas most traditional factors are less inclined to do business with small clients and customers, American Factor thrives on making these companies grow and prosper.   Our mission is to help businesses grow by improving their cash flow through invoice factoring. For over 30 years, we have provided our clients with professional and friendly factoring services with an emphasis on effective communication and customer satisfaction. Our clients' growth drives the success of our company.   Starting out as a small financing firm ourselves, we are proud of forming symbiotic relationships with our clients, in which all parties can reap the benefits of maximizing their business potential. Our unique flat rate system and unmatched customer service exemplify our partnership goals by never surprising our clients with hidden or additional fees and treating your customer base with the utmost respect. As our client, we want you to focus on creating opportunities, increasing profits, and growing your business instead of worrying about customers, late payments, and tight cash flows.

Description: Creating & Discovering Design
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: OUR MISSION  BYCO is a platform for creating, discovering, and shopping good design.  For designers, BYCO is a one-stop-shop, where anyone can submit designs for men’s and women’s clothing and home accessories. BYCO handles the sampling, production, distribution, photography, marketing, and sales with designers receiving 20-30% of the sales from their designs.  For shoppers, BYCO offers innovative and quality-made design, made in limited edition, with some of the most talented designers from around the world.  HOW DOES BYCO WORK  For designers, BYCO works in 2 ways:  For our “pro” level designers, BYCO offers sampling and a cost-efficient price, where for as little as $150.00, anyone can create and receive a custom made piece, and receive 30% of the sales from his or her design.  For our standard designers, BYCO posts the design submission to our Discovery page, where the community can cover the cost of the sample; in exchange, the designer receives 20% of sales, and funders receive a discount towards any BYCO purchase.  WHO IS BYCO FOR  BYCO is only interested in good design – and that may come from anyone and anywhere.  Established designers who would like a more self-branded presence can customize their profile page to act as a SHOP site and sell directly to their customers.  For newer designers, the BYCO Shop page is a great way to gain exposure and sell your wares to the BYCO community.
Industry Groups: Clothing and Apparel, Commerce and Shopping, Design, Financial Services, Other
